\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. T. praecox} Wulfen in Jacq., {\i Collect. Bot.}{\b  2}: 124 (1789) ({\i T. affine} sensu Boiss., non Schott & Kotschy). Stems (5-)10-20(-35) cm, erect, glabrous, more or less glaucous. Rosette-leaves oblong to broadly ovate, petiolate, often violet beneath; cauline leaves ovate-oblong, amplexicaul with obtuse auricles; all entire or sinuate-denticulate, coriaceous. Inflorescence much elongating in fruit. Sepals 2-3 mm, violet-tipped; petals 5-7 mm, narrow, white. Silicula usually 7-9 mm, narrowly obcordate; angle at base of notch not more than 90°; style (1-)2-3·5 mm, always exceeding the notch at least slightly. Seeds 2-4 in each loculus.{\i  Stony, shady slopes and dry grassland. S. Europe,from S.E. France to Krym.} Al Au Bu Ga Gr It Ju Rs(K) Tu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  praecox}: Rosette-leaves oblong to broadly ovate; cauline leaves ovate. Style (1-)2-3·5 mm. 2n = 14.{\i  Throughout the range of the species}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp.{\b  cuneifolium} (Griseb. ex Pant.) Clapham,{\i  Feddes Repert.}{\b  70}: 4 (1964) ({\i T. cuneifolium} Griseb. ex Pant.): Rosette-leaves ovate-cuneate to spathulate; cauline leaves oblong. Style 2-4 mm.{\i  S. Jugoslavia, Albania and S.W. Bulgaria.}
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 {\b T. albanicum} (F.K. Meyer) Greuter & Burdet,{\i  Willdenowia}{\b  13}: 95 (1983) and{\i  T. cikaeum} (F.K. Meyer) Greuter & Burdet,{\i  loc. cit.} (1983), from the mountains of Albania, may represent variants of {\b 15}.
\par

