\pard\f0\fs28 {\b T. lutescens} Velen., {\i Sitz.-Ber. Böhm. Ges. Wiss.}{\b  1903} ({\b 28}): 2 (1904), a non-stoloniferous, somewhat glaucous, glabrous perennial, with erect stems 12-15 cm, and obovate, abruptly petiolate rosette-leaves, from N. Greece (Macedonia), is possibly not distinct from {\b 19}.
